Enum Class eLeapEventType

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<eLeapEventType>
komposten.leapjna.leapc.enums.eLeapEventType
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<eLeapEventType>, Constable, Enums.IntEnum
public enum eLeapEventType extends Enum<eLeapEventType> implements Enums.IntEnum
The types of event messages resulting from calling LeapC.LeapPollConnection(Pointer, int, LEAP_CONNECTION_MESSAGE).
Since:
LeapJna 1.0.0, Ultraleap Orion SDK 3.0.0

  • Enum Constant Details

    • Unknown

      public static final eLeapEventType Unknown
      Indicates that an unknown event type, i.e. one which doesn't match any of the constants, was encountered.

    • None

      public static final eLeapEventType None
      No event has occurred within the timeout period specified when calling LeapC.LeapPollConnection(Pointer, int, LEAP_CONNECTION_MESSAGE).

    • Connection

      public static final eLeapEventType Connection
      A connection to the Ultraleap Tracking Service has been established.

    • ConnectionLost

      public static final eLeapEventType ConnectionLost
      The connection to the Ultraleap Tracking Service has been lost.

    • Device

      public static final eLeapEventType Device

      A device has been detected or plugged-in.

      A device event is dispatched after a connection is established for any devices already plugged in. (The system currently only supports one streaming device at a time.)

    • DeviceFailure

      public static final eLeapEventType DeviceFailure

      A device has failed.

      Device failure could be caused by hardware failure, USB controller issues, or other system instability. Note that unplugging a device generates an DeviceLost event message, not a failure message.

    • Policy

      public static final eLeapEventType Policy

      A policy change has occurred.

      This can be due to setting a policy with LeapC.LeapSetPolicyFlags(Pointer, long, long) or due to changing policy-related config settings, including images_mode. (A user can also change these policies using the Ultraleap Tracking Control Panel.)

    • Tracking

      public static final eLeapEventType Tracking
      A tracking frame. The message contains the tracking data for the frame.

    • ImageRequestError

      public static final eLeapEventType ImageRequestError

      The request for an image has failed.

      The message contains information about the failure. The client application will not receive the requested image set.

    • ImageComplete

      public static final eLeapEventType ImageComplete

      The request for an image is complete.

      The image data has been completely written to the application-provided buffer.

    • LogEvent

      public static final eLeapEventType LogEvent
      A system message.

    • DeviceLost

      public static final eLeapEventType DeviceLost

      The device connection has been lost.

      This event is generally asserted when the device has been detached from the system, when the connection to the service has been lost, or if the device is closed while streaming. Generally, any event where the system can conclude no further frames will be received will result in this message. The DeviceEvent field will be filled with the id of the formerly attached device.

    • ConfigResponse

      public static final eLeapEventType ConfigResponse
      The asynchronous response to a call to LeapC.LeapRequestConfigValue(Pointer, String, LongByReference). Contains the value of requested configuration item.

    • ConfigChange

      public static final eLeapEventType ConfigChange
      The asynchronous response to a call to LeapC.LeapSaveConfigValue(Pointer, String, LEAP_VARIANT, LongByReference). Reports whether the change succeeded or failed.

    • DeviceStatusChange

      public static final eLeapEventType DeviceStatusChange
      Notification that a status change has been detected on an attached device

    • DroppedFrame

      public static final eLeapEventType DroppedFrame

    • Image

      public static final eLeapEventType Image
      Notification that an unrequested stereo image pair is available

    • PointMappingChange

      public static final eLeapEventType PointMappingChange
      Notification that point mapping has changed

    • TrackingMode

      public static final eLeapEventType TrackingMode
      A tracking mode change has occurred. This can be due to changing the hmd or screentop policy with LeapC.LeapSetPolicyFlags(Pointer, long, long). or setting the tracking mode using LeapC.LeapSetTrackingMode(Pointer, int).
      Since:
      1.1.0 (Gemini 5.0.0)

    • LogEvents

      public static final eLeapEventType LogEvents
      An array of system messages.

    • HeadPose

      public static final eLeapEventType HeadPose
      A head pose. The message contains the timestamped head position and orientation.

    • Eyes

      public static final eLeapEventType Eyes
      Tracked eye positions.

    • IMU

      public static final eLeapEventType IMU
      An IMU reading.
